wfxnsidpForwarding.name: wfxnsidpForwarding
wfxnsidpForwarding.description: Indicates whether the node is a router.

wfxnsidpInReceives.name: wfxnsidpInReceives
wfxnsidpInReceives.description: Contains the total number of all IDP datagrams (including those received in error) received from all interfaces.

wfxnsidpInHdrErrors.name: wfxnsidpInHdrErrors
wfxnsidpInHdrErrors.description: Contains the number of IDP datagrams discarded because of errors in their IDP headers. Such errors include bad checksums, format errors and bad hop counts.

wfxnsidpInAddrErrors.name: wfxnsidpInAddrErrors
wfxnsidpInAddrErrors.description: The number of IDP datagrams discarded because of invalid destination fields.

wfxnsidpForwDatagrams.name: wfxnsidpForwDatagrams
wfxnsidpForwDatagrams.description: The number of received IDP datagrams not addressed to the XNS router. The router attempts to forward these datagrams to their ultimate destination.

wfxnsidpInUnknownProtos.name: wfxnsidpInUnknownProtos
wfxnsidpInUnknownProtos.description: The number of IDP datagrams discarded because of an invalid protocol field.

wfxnsidpInDiscards.name: wfxnsidpInDiscards
wfxnsidpInDiscards.description: The number of input IDP datagrams discarded because of of insufficient Server resources.

wfxnsidpInDelivers.name: wfxnsidpInDelivers
wfxnsidpInDelivers.description: The number of IDP datagrams delivered to the IDP user protocols. (Error, Echo, RIP).

wfxnsidpOutRequests.name: wfxnsidpOutRequests
wfxnsidpOutRequests.description: The number of IDP datagrams generated by the local IDP user protocols.

wfxnsidpOutDiscards.name: wfxnsidpOutDiscards
wfxnsidpOutDiscards.description: The number of output IDP datagrams discarded because of of insufficient Server resources.

wfxnsidpOutNoRoutes.name: wfxnsidpOutNoRoutes
wfxnsidpOutNoRoutes.description: The number of IDP datagrams discarded because no route could be found for their destination.

wfxnsidpErrSupressed.name: wfxnsidpErrSupressed
wfxnsidpErrSupressed.description: The number of packet dropped because their length is below minimum.

wfxnsidpErrDestUnspec.name: wfxnsidpErrDestUnspec
wfxnsidpErrDestUnspec.description: The number of destination-host-generated Error packets with an Error Number of 0 relayed by the router. This indicates an IDP packet rejected for unspecified reasons.

wfxnsidpErrDestHdrLen.name: wfxnsidpErrDestHdrLen
wfxnsidpErrDestHdrLen.description: The number of packets rejected by a destination host because the packet header was of insufficient length.

wfxnsidpErrDestProto.name: wfxnsidpErrDestProto
wfxnsidpErrDestProto.description: The number of packets rejected by a destination host because the protocol type field contained an invalid or unknown value.

wfxnsidpErrDestCksum.name: wfxnsidpErrDestCksum
wfxnsidpErrDestCksum.description: The number of packets rejected by a destination host because of a faulty or corrupted IDP checksum.

wfxnsidpErrDestBadSock.name: wfxnsidpErrDestBadSock
wfxnsidpErrDestBadSock.description: The number of packets rejected by a destination host because the packet was addressed to an unknown socket.

wfxnsidpErrDestNoResrcs.name: wfxnsidpErrDestNoResrcs
wfxnsidpErrDestNoResrcs.description: The number of packets rejected by a destination host because of a lack of processing resources.

wfxnsidpErrDestXitUnspec.name: wfxnsidpErrDestXitUnspec
wfxnsidpErrDestXitUnspec.description: The number of packets rejected by the router for unspecified reasons.

wfxnsidpErrXitCksum.name: wfxnsidpErrXitCksum
wfxnsidpErrXitCksum.description: The number of packets rejected by the router because of a faulty or corrupted checksum.

wfxnsidpErrXitUnreach.name: wfxnsidpErrXitUnreach
wfxnsidpErrXitUnreach.description: The number of packets rejected by the router because the destination is unreachable.

wfxnsidpErrXitHopCnt.name: wfxnsidpErrXitHopCnt
wfxnsidpErrXitHopCnt.description: The number of packets rejected by the router becuase the packet had passed through more than the maximum number of routers before arriving at its destination.

wfxnsidpErrXitTooBig.name: wfxnsidpErrXitTooBig
wfxnsidpErrXitTooBig.description: The number of packets rejected by the router becuase the packet was too long for the router to relay.

wfxnsidpAddrEntry.name: wfxnsidpAddrEntry
wfxnsidpAddrEntry.description: An entry in the IDP address table.

wfxnsidpRouteEntry.name: wfxnsidpRouteEntry
wfxnsidpRouteEntry.description: Information about a routing table entry.

wfxnsidpRouteIfIndex.name: wfxnsidpRouteIfIndex
wfxnsidpRouteIfIndex.description: An index to the next hop interface.

wfxnsidpRouteMetric.name: wfxnsidpRouteMetric
wfxnsidpRouteMetric.description: The RIP hop count to the destination. 0 means the host is locally attached.

wfxnsidpRouteNextHop.name: wfxnsidpRouteNextHop
wfxnsidpRouteNextHop.description: The host address of the next hop gateway.

wfxnsidpRouteType.name: wfxnsidpRouteType
wfxnsidpRouteType.description: Indicates whether the route was statically configured, direct or learned via RIP.

wfxnsidpRouteProto.name: wfxnsidpRouteProto
wfxnsidpRouteProto.description: The actual routing protocol used to determine the route.

wfxnsidpRouteAge.name: wfxnsidpRouteAge
wfxnsidpRouteAge.description: The age (in seconds) of the route.

wfdrsState.name: wfdrsState
wfdrsState.description: Indicates the state of the router.

wfdrsArea.name: wfdrsArea
wfdrsArea.description: The number of the local DECNET area.

wfdrsMaxArea.name: wfdrsMaxArea
wfdrsMaxArea.description: The maximum number of areas in the network.

wfdrsMaxNode.name: wfdrsMaxNode
wfdrsMaxNode.description: The maximum number of nodes in any area.

wfdrsAreaMaxHop.name: wfdrsAreaMaxHop
wfdrsAreaMaxHop.description: Maximum number of areas a packet can transit from source to destination.

wfdrsNodeMaxHop.name: wfdrsNodeMaxHop
wfdrsNodeMaxHop.description: The maximum number of hops a packet can transit from source to destination.

wfdrsMaxVisits.name: wfdrsMaxVisits
wfdrsMaxVisits.description: Maximum number of times packet can transit the same router.

wfdrsRoutingTimer.name: wfdrsRoutingTimer
wfdrsRoutingTimer.description: Time interval between topology packets on non-broadcast media.

wfdrsBcastRoutTimer.name: wfdrsBcastRoutTimer
wfdrsBcastRoutTimer.description: Time interval between topology packets on bradcast media.

wfdrsIfTabEntry.name: wfdrsIfTabEntry
wfdrsIfTabEntry.description: An entry in the DECNET interface table.

wfdrsIfTabEntName.name: wfdrsIfTabEntName
wfdrsIfTabEntName.description: The circuit group name for this interface.

wfdrsIfTabEntCost.name: wfdrsIfTabEntCost
wfdrsIfTabEntCost.description: The DECNET circuit cost for this interface.

wfdrsIfTabEntHelloTimr.name: wfdrsIfTabEntHelloTimr
wfdrsIfTabEntHelloTimr.description: The time interval between DECNET hello packets.

wfdrsIfTabEntNumRtrs.name: wfdrsIfTabEntNumRtrs
wfdrsIfTabEntNumRtrs.description: Maximum number of adjacent routers on this interface.

wfdrsAreaRoute.name: wfdrsAreaRoute
wfdrsAreaRoute.description: Information about a route to an area.

wfdrsAreaRouteCost.name: wfdrsAreaRouteCost
wfdrsAreaRouteCost.description: Aggregate cost to reach destination area.

wfdrsAreaRouteHopCount.name: wfdrsAreaRouteHopCount
wfdrsAreaRouteHopCount.description: Number of hops to reach destination area.

wfdrsAreaRouteNextArea.name: wfdrsAreaRouteNextArea
wfdrsAreaRouteNextArea.description: The next area to forward the packet.

wfdrsAreaRouteNextNode.name: wfdrsAreaRouteNextNode
wfdrsAreaRouteNextNode.description: The next node to forward the packet to.

wfdrsAreaRouteIf.name: wfdrsAreaRouteIf
wfdrsAreaRouteIf.description: The interface to forward the packet on.

wfdrsNodeRoute.name: wfdrsNodeRoute
wfdrsNodeRoute.description: Information about how to reach an node within the area.

wfdrsNodeRouteCost.name: wfdrsNodeRouteCost
wfdrsNodeRouteCost.description: The aggregate cost to the destination node.

wfdrsNodeRouteHopCount.name: wfdrsNodeRouteHopCount
wfdrsNodeRouteHopCount.description: Number of hops to destination node.

wfdrsNodeRouteNextHop.name: wfdrsNodeRouteNextHop
wfdrsNodeRouteNextHop.description: The node number of the next hop.

wfdrsNodeRouteIf.name: wfdrsNodeRouteIf
wfdrsNodeRouteIf.description: The interface index of the next hop.

wflbFwdTable.name: wflbFwdTable
wflbFwdTable.description: The bridge modules's table of MAC address-interface mappings.

wflbFwdEntry.name: wflbFwdEntry
wflbFwdEntry.description: Each entry describes one MAC address-interface mapping; that is, each entry describes a station which has been or is being learned.

wflbFwdEntIf.name: wflbFwdEntIf
wflbFwdEntIf.description: A number identifying the interface on which the station addressed by wflbFwdEntMacAddr was learned. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wflbFwdEntMacAddr.name: wflbFwdEntMacAddr
wflbFwdEntMacAddr.description: The MAC-level (physical) address of the station described by this wflbFwdEntry.

wflbFwdEntSrcDisp.name: wflbFwdEntSrcDisp
wflbFwdEntSrcDisp.description: Identifies the disposition of frames containing wflbFwdEntMacAddr as the source address field of the frame. 0 signifies drop; 1 signifies forward.

wflbFwdEntDstDisp.name: wflbFwdEntDstDisp
wflbFwdEntDstDisp.description: Identifies the disposition of frames containing wflbFwdEntMacAddr as the destination address field of the frame. 0 signifies drop; 1 signifies forward.

wflbFwdEntIfName.name: wflbFwdEntIfName
wflbFwdEntIfName.description: A text string contining the circuit group name of interface wflbFwdEntIf.

wflbFwdEntFloodStat.name: wflbFwdEntFloodStat
wflbFwdEntFloodStat.description: Denotes whether frames destined for wflbFwdEntMacAddr are being flooded or dropped if the MAC Address-interface mapping for wflbFwdEntMacAddr has not yet been learned. If the value of wflbFwdEntFloodStat is forwarding(1), the MAC Address-interface mapping has been learned.

wflbRifTable.name: wflbRifTable
wflbRifTable.description: The bridge modules's source routing RIF (Routing Information Field) table.

wflbRifEntry.name: wflbRifEntry
wflbRifEntry.description: Each entry contains a RIF cache for a network node. The table is indexed by an arbitrary set of 6 integers.

wflbRifMacSrcAddress.name: wflbRifMacSrcAddress
wflbRifMacSrcAddress.description: The MAC-level (physical) address of the source interface.

wflbRifMacAddress.name: wflbRifMacAddress
wflbRifMacAddress.description: The MAC-level (physical) address of the destination interface.

wflbRifCg.name: wflbRifCg
wflbRifCg.description: The name of the circuit group that connects the source interface to token ring.

wflbRif.name: wflbRif
wflbRif.description: A description of the path used to source route packets between the source route and the destination. The first two bytes contain the routing control (RC) field that describes the routing type, field length, direction bit and largest frame size as follows. bits 1-2: RIF type 00: Specifically Routed Frame (SRF) 11: Spanning Tree Explorer (STE) 10: All Routes Explorer (ARE) bit 3: Reserved bits 4-8: Length of RIF Maximum = 18 bytes bit 9: Direction that frames traverses LAN 0: Forward 1: Reverse bits 10-12: Largest Frame size for this route Maximum is 4472 bytes bits 13-16: Reserved Next are a series of two-byte route descriptors; each contains a 12-bit LAN ID followed by a 4-bit bridge ID number which indicate the next hop in the route.

wftftpFilesIn.name: wftftpFilesIn
wftftpFilesIn.description: The number of successful transfers of files to this entity since the system was last initialized.

wftftpFilesOut.name: wftftpFilesOut
wftftpFilesOut.description: The number of successful transfers of files from this entity since the system was last initialized.

wftftpWRQIn.name: wftftpWRQIn
wftftpWRQIn.description: The number of WRQ PDUs received by the TFTP entity since the system was last initialized. This is the number of requests to deposit a file made by a remote TFTP client.

wftftpWRQOut.name: wftftpWRQOut
wftftpWRQOut.description: The number of WRQ PDUs sent by the TFTP entity since the system was last initialized. This is the number of requests made by this system to send a file to a remote TFTP client.

wftftpRRQIn.name: wftftpRRQIn
wftftpRRQIn.description: The number of RRQ PDUs received by the TFTP entity since the system was last initialized. This is the number of requests to retreive a file made by a remote TFTP client.

wftftpRRQOut.name: wftftpRRQOut
wftftpRRQOut.description: The number of RRQ PDUs sent by the TFTP entity since the system was last initialized. This is the number of requests made by this system to retrieve a file from a remote TFTP client.

wftftpRxmits.name: wftftpRxmits
wftftpRxmits.description: The number of TFTP PDUs that have been retransmitted by this entity.

wftftpERRIn.name: wftftpERRIn
wftftpERRIn.description: The number of ERR PDUs received by the TFTP entity since the system was last initialized.

wftftpERROut.name: wftftpERROut
wftftpERROut.description: The number of ERR PDUs sent by the TFTP entity since the system was last initialized.

wftftpAborts.name: wftftpAborts
wftftpAborts.description: The number of unsuccessful TFTP file transfer that have been abnormally terminated.

wfappleStationRouting.name: wfappleStationRouting
wfappleStationRouting.description: Indicates whether this entity is routing (i.e., forwarding) AppleTalk datagrams. 1 signifies forwarding; 0 not forwarding.

wfappleStationVersion.name: wfappleStationVersion
wfappleStationVersion.description: The version number of the AppleTalk protocol supported by this entity (i.e., Wellfleet supports Version 2).

wfapplePortTable.name: wfapplePortTable
wfapplePortTable.description: The wfapplePortTable is a table of per-interface AppleTalk Configuration parameters. An interface will have a corresponding entry in this table only if AppleTalk routing is defined for that interface.

wfapplePortEntry.name: wfapplePortEntry
wfapplePortEntry.description: Each entry describes an interface of the AppleTalk Router.

wfapplePortIfIndex.name: wfapplePortIfIndex
wfapplePortIfIndex.description: A number identifying the interface described by this wfapplePortEntry. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wfapplePortSeed.name: wfapplePortSeed
wfapplePortSeed.description: Describes whether this interface was configured as a 'seed' port. 1 indicates a seed port; 0 a non-seed port.

wfapplePortMinNet.name: wfapplePortMinNet
wfapplePortMinNet.description: The minimum network number in the range of network numbers assigned to this interface.

wfapplePortMaxNet.name: wfapplePortMaxNet
wfapplePortMaxNet.description: The maximum network number in the range of network numbers assigned to this interface.

wfapplePortNetwork.name: wfapplePortNetwork
wfapplePortNetwork.description: The network number within the range wfapplePortMinNet to wfapplePortMaxNet which is assigned to the network attached to this interface.

wfapplePortNodeID.name: wfapplePortNodeID
wfapplePortNodeID.description: The node identification which denotes this AppleTalk entity on network wfapplePortNetwork. The pair (wfapplePortNetwork, wfapplePortNodeID) constitutes a complete AppleTalk address.

wfapplePortDefaultZone.name: wfapplePortDefaultZone
wfapplePortDefaultZone.description: The name of the default zone for this interface (a zero-length string means that no default zone was assigned to this interface.

wfappleDDPPktsIn.name: wfappleDDPPktsIn
wfappleDDPPktsIn.description: The total number of DDP packets received by this entity.

wfappleDDPPktsOut.name: wfappleDDPPktsOut
wfappleDDPPktsOut.description: The total number of DDP packets transmitted by this entity.

wfappleDDPPktsFwd.name: wfappleDDPPktsFwd
wfappleDDPPktsFwd.description: The total number of DDP packets forwarded by this entity.

wfappleDDPDelivers.name: wfappleDDPDelivers
wfappleDDPDelivers.description: The total number of DDP packets received by this entity which were delivered to a higher-layer AppleTalk protocol for processing.

wfappleDDPUnknownNet.name: wfappleDDPUnknownNet
wfappleDDPUnknownNet.description: The total number of DDP packets discarded by this entity because the destination network to which the packet was directed was unknown.

wfappleDDPHopsExceeded.name: wfappleDDPHopsExceeded
wfappleDDPHopsExceeded.description: The total number of DDP packets discarded by this entity because the packet's hop count exceeded 15.

wfappleDDPBadChksum.name: wfappleDDPBadChksum
wfappleDDPBadChksum.description: The total number of DDP packets discarded by this entity because the contained an incorrect DDP checksum.

wfappleDDPDropped.name: wfappleDDPDropped
wfappleDDPDropped.description: The total number of DDP packets discarded by this entity.

wfappleEchoRequestIn.name: wfappleEchoRequestIn
wfappleEchoRequestIn.description: The number of AEP Echo Request Packets received by this entity.

wfappleEchoResponseOut.name: wfappleEchoResponseOut
wfappleEchoResponseOut.description: The number of AEP Echo Response Packets sent by this entity.

wfappleRTMPRequestIn.name: wfappleRTMPRequestIn
wfappleRTMPRequestIn.description: The total number of RTMP Request packets received by this entity.

wfappleRTMPResponseOut.name: wfappleRTMPResponseOut
wfappleRTMPResponseOut.description: The total number of RTMP Response packets transmitted by this entity.

wfappleRoutingTable.name: wfappleRoutingTable
wfappleRoutingTable.description: The AppleTalk Routing Table contains an entry for each AppleTalk Route known to this entity.

wfappleRouteEntry.name: wfappleRouteEntry
wfappleRouteEntry.description: A route to a particular AppleTalk destination.

wfappleRouteMinNet.name: wfappleRouteMinNet
wfappleRouteMinNet.description: The minimum network number in the destination's network number range.

wfappleRouteMaxNet.name: wfappleRouteMaxNet
wfappleRouteMaxNet.description: The maximum network number in the destination's network number range.

wfappleRouteIfIndex.name: wfappleRouteIfIndex
wfappleRouteIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wfappleRouteDistance.name: wfappleRouteDistance
wfappleRouteDistance.description: The AppleTalk routing metric for this route.

wfappleRouteNextNet.name: wfappleRouteNextNet
wfappleRouteNextNet.description: The network number of the Next Hop Router for this destination.

wfappleRouteNextNode.name: wfappleRouteNextNode
wfappleRouteNextNode.description: The node identification of the Next Hop Router for this destination.

wfappleRouteState.name: wfappleRouteState
wfappleRouteState.description: The status of this route. Valid routes are marked Good (2); invalidated or timed-out routes (if present) are marked Bad (0); a Suspect route (1) is still valid for routing but has been noted as marginal.

wfappleNBPFwdReqOut.name: wfappleNBPFwdReqOut
wfappleNBPFwdReqOut.description: The number of NBP Forward Request packets transmitted by this entity.

wfappleNBPLookupOut.name: wfappleNBPLookupOut
wfappleNBPLookupOut.description: The number of NBP Lookup packets transmitted by this entity.

wfappleNBPBcastReqIn.name: wfappleNBPBcastReqIn
wfappleNBPBcastReqIn.description: The number of NBP Broadcast Request packets received by this entity.

wfappleNBPFwdReqIn.name: wfappleNBPFwdReqIn
wfappleNBPFwdReqIn.description: The number of NBP Forward Request packets received by this entity.

wfappleZIPRequestOut.name: wfappleZIPRequestOut
wfappleZIPRequestOut.description: The number of Zone Information Protocol (ZIP) Request packets transmitted by this entity.

wfappleZIPReplyOut.name: wfappleZIPReplyOut
wfappleZIPReplyOut.description: The number of Zone Information Protocol (ZIP) Reply packets transmitted by this entity.

wfappleZIPNetInfoRepOut.name: wfappleZIPNetInfoRepOut
wfappleZIPNetInfoRepOut.description: The number of ZIP GetNetInfo Reply packets transmitted by this entity.

wfappleZIPGetLclZoneOut.name: wfappleZIPGetLclZoneOut
wfappleZIPGetLclZoneOut.description: The number of ZIP GetLocalZones packets transmitted by this entity.

wfappleZIPGetLclZoneRepOut.name: wfappleZIPGetLclZoneRepOut
wfappleZIPGetLclZoneRepOut.description: The number of ZIP GetLocalZones Reply packets transmitted by this entity.

wfappleZIPGetZoneListOut.name: wfappleZIPGetZoneListOut
wfappleZIPGetZoneListOut.description: The number of ZIP GetZoneList packets transmitted by this entity.

wfappleZIPGetNetInfoOut.name: wfappleZIPGetNetInfoOut
wfappleZIPGetNetInfoOut.description: The number of ZIP GetNetInfo packets transmitted by this entity.

wfappleZIPGetNetInfoIn.name: wfappleZIPGetNetInfoIn
wfappleZIPGetNetInfoIn.description: The number of ZIP GetNetInfo packets received by this entity.

wfappleZIPNetInfoRepIn.name: wfappleZIPNetInfoRepIn
wfappleZIPNetInfoRepIn.description: The number of ZIP GetNetInfo Reply packets received by this entity.

wfappleZIPRequestIn.name: wfappleZIPRequestIn
wfappleZIPRequestIn.description: The number of ZIP Request packets received by this entity.

wfappleZIPReplyIn.name: wfappleZIPReplyIn
wfappleZIPReplyIn.description: The number of ZIP Reply packets received by this entity.

wfappleZIPGetZoneListIn.name: wfappleZIPGetZoneListIn
wfappleZIPGetZoneListIn.description: The number of ZIP GetZoneList packets received by this entity.

wfappleZIPGetLclZoneIn.name: wfappleZIPGetLclZoneIn
wfappleZIPGetLclZoneIn.description: The number of ZIP GetLocalZones packets received by this entity.

wfappleZIPGetLclZoneRepIn.name: wfappleZIPGetLclZoneRepIn
wfappleZIPGetLclZoneRepIn.description: The number of ZIP GetLocalZones Reply packets received by this entity.

wfappleLocalZoneTable.name: wfappleLocalZoneTable
wfappleLocalZoneTable.description: A list of all the zone names for the network to which the entity is connected.

wfappleLZTEntry.name: wfappleLZTEntry
wfappleLZTEntry.description: Each entry associates a zone name with an interface.

wfappleLZTZoneName.name: wfappleLZTZoneName
wfappleLZTZoneName.description: The name of an AppleTalk zone associated with a particular interface of the AppleTalk router.

wfappleLZTIfIndex.name: wfappleLZTIfIndex
wfappleLZTIfIndex.description: The interface to the network with which the named zone is associated. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wfappleAARPTable.name: wfappleAARPTable
wfappleAARPTable.description: The AppleTalk Address Resolution Protocol Table used for mapping from AppleTalk Net/Node addresses to physical addresses.

wfappleAARPEntry.name: wfappleAARPEntry
wfappleAARPEntry.description: Each entry contains one AppleTalk Net/Node address to 'physical' address equivalence.

wfappleAARPNet.name: wfappleAARPNet
wfappleAARPNet.description: The network number of the AppleTalk entity described by this address equivalence.

wfappleAARPNode.name: wfappleAARPNode
wfappleAARPNode.description: The node identification of the AppleTalk entity described by this address equivalence.

wfappleAARPMacAddress.name: wfappleAARPMacAddress
wfappleAARPMacAddress.description: The media-dependent 'physical' address of this AppleTalk entity.

wfappleAARPIfIndex.name: wfappleAARPIfIndex
wfappleAARPIfIndex.description: The interface on which this entry's equivalence is effective. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

wfconfigVersionMajor.name: wfconfigVersionMajor
wfconfigVersionMajor.description: The Major Version Number of the Software Release running in the Communications Server.

wfconfigVersionMinor.name: wfconfigVersionMinor
wfconfigVersionMinor.description: The Minor Version Number of the Software Release running in the Communications Server.

wfconfigImageFileName.name: wfconfigImageFileName
wfconfigImageFileName.description: The name of the binary load image file from which the Communications Server was loaded.

wfconfigConfigFileName.name: wfconfigConfigFileName
wfconfigConfigFileName.description: The name of the text file from which the current configuration of the Communications Server was read.

wfconfigKeysBridge.name: wfconfigKeysBridge
wfconfigKeysBridge.description: Indicates whether the Bridge software option is active in the Communications Server's software configuration. 0 indicates that the option is absent; 1 that it is present.

wfconfigKeysDrs.name: wfconfigKeysDrs
wfconfigKeysDrs.description: Indicates whether the DecNet routing software option is active in the Communications Server's software configuration. 0 indicates that the option is absent; 1 that it is present.

wfconfigKeysIp.name: wfconfigKeysIp
wfconfigKeysIp.description: Indicates whether the Ip routing software option is active in the Communications Server's software configuration. 0 indicates that the option is absent; 1 that it is present.

wfconfigKeysX25.name: wfconfigKeysX25
wfconfigKeysX25.description: Indicates whether the X.25 software option is active in the Communications Server's software configuration. 0 indicates that the option is absent; 1 that it is present.

wfconfigKeysXns.name: wfconfigKeysXns
wfconfigKeysXns.description: Indicates whether the XNS/IPX routing software option is active in the Communications Server's software configuration. 0 indicates that the option is absent; 1 that it is present.

wfconfigKeysApple.name: wfconfigKeysApple
wfconfigKeysApple.description: Indicates whether the AppleTalk routing software option is active in the Communications Server's software configuration. 0 indicates that the option is absent; 1 that it is present.

wfconfigHwTable.name: wfconfigHwTable
wfconfigHwTable.description: The Hw Table records the Hardware present in the Communications Server.

wfconfigHwEntry.name: wfconfigHwEntry
wfconfigHwEntry.description: Describes the Processor and ILI Cards present in a slot of the Communications Server. Slots are numbered from 1 to n, and there may be gaps. Conventionally, the System Controller and Floppy I/O module are present in slot 1.

wfconfigHwAceSn.name: wfconfigHwAceSn
wfconfigHwAceSn.description: The serial number of the processor board in this slot. Conventionally the processor board in slot 1 is not an ACE but a System Controller.

wfconfigHwAceRev.name: wfconfigHwAceRev
wfconfigHwAceRev.description: The revision level of the processor board in this slot. Conventionally the processor board in slot 1 is not an ACE but a System Controller.

wfconfigHwModSn.name: wfconfigHwModSn
wfconfigHwModSn.description: The serial number of the ILI board (Link Module) in this slot.

wfconfigHwModRev.name: wfconfigHwModRev
wfconfigHwModRev.description: The revision level of the ILI board (Link Module) in this slot.

wfconfigHwModID.name: wfconfigHwModID
wfconfigHwModID.description: The ID number of the ILI board (Link Module) in this slot. ID numbers are documented in section A.13 of the Operator's Guide.

wfconfigHwSlot.name: wfconfigHwSlot
wfconfigHwSlot.description: The slot in which the boards described in this entry are present. Slots are numbered from 1, and there need not be processor-ILI pair in every slot. wfconfigHwEntrys will be defined only for populated slots.

wfconfigBootpRqSrvr.name: wfconfigBootpRqSrvr
wfconfigBootpRqSrvr.description: The IP Address of the BOOTP Server which initialized the entity's Load Image and Configuration name.

wfconfigBootpFileSrvr.name: wfconfigBootpFileSrvr
wfconfigBootpFileSrvr.description: The IP Address of the TFTP Server from which the entity's Load Image and Configuration file were downloaded.

wfipxidpForwarding.name: wfipxidpForwarding
wfipxidpForwarding.description: Indicates whether the node is a router.

wfipxidpInReceives.name: wfipxidpInReceives
